rComments: Just study and ask for help if you need it

She is very caring and understanding. I was failing her course, but thanks to her, I passed it with a decent grade. Her explanations are clear and concise and she gives good examples. What many students do wrong is approach her when its too late. If you need or want help, go to her asap. Do not wait until the last minute to seek her assistance.
She'll baby you for the midterm, but be warned for her final. You get a false sense of security that it's a watered down version of A37, but the final will have the unsuspecting student bawling.
She was trying her best to explain the content. Tick accent but still understandable
She always tries to explain everything clearly, but her accent is too strong, so i can hardly understand. Overall, she is a good prof.

She is the best prof ever. I took her this summer and I ended up with an A+ and 95 on my final Exam. I only went to her first class. Her class is a walk in the park. She doesn't teach you that well but her tests are straight forward and easy. Make sure she is making the tests and the exam.
